%pyspark
# Q2.3.1
from pyspark.sql import *

#DataFrame as a SQL temporary view
df.createOrReplaceTempView("tempory_view")
# get property owners 
owners = spark.sql("select host_id, host_name, COUNT(*) as no_of_prop from tempory_view group by host_id, host_name Order by no_of_prop DESC")
 ##Get the owners total
owners_count=owners.count()
multi_prop_owners = spark.sql("select host_id, host_name, COUNT(*) as no_of_prop from tempory_view group by host_id, host_name HAVING no_of_prop>1 Order by no_of_prop DESC")
multi_prop_owners_count = multi_prop_owners.count()
percentage = (float(multi_prop_owners_count)/owners_count)*100.0
print("Percentage of owners who have more than one property: ")
print(percentage)

%pyspark

# columns
columns=['id','latitude','longitude','neighbourhood_group']
training_df = df.select(columns)
#training_df.show()
training_df = training_df.na.drop()
training_df = training_df.withColumn("longitude", training_df["longitude"].cast(DoubleType()))
training_df.printSchema()

training_df.createOrReplaceTempView("listings_columns")

training_df_detailed = spark.sql("select neighbourhood_group, count(id) id_count from listings_columns group by neighbourhood_group order by id_count DESC")
training_df_detailed.show()

#ignore minimul popular regions
def getPopularity(region):
    if region=='Central Region': return 1
    elif region=='East Region': return 2
    elif region=='North Region': return 3
    elif region=='North-East Region': return 4
    elif region=='West Region': return  5
    else: return 6
    
udfToInt = udf(getPopularity, IntegerType())
training_df_detailed = training_df.withColumn("popularity", udfToInt("neighbourhood_group"))

popularity_df = training_df_detailed.filter(training_df_detailed['popularity'] < 6)
popularity_df.show()

%pyspark
from pyspark.ml.feature import StandardScaler

featureCols=['latitude','longitude']
featuredf = popularity_df.select(featureCols).show()

def getVector(df,featureCols):
	assembler = VectorAssembler(inputCols=featureCols,outputCol="features")
	vector=assembler.transform(df)
	return vector
	
vectorDf=getVector(popularity_df,featureCols)
vectorDf.show()

input_df = vectorDf.select('popularity', 'features')

scaler = StandardScaler(inputCol='features', outputCol='scaledFeatures', withStd=True, withMean=True)
scalerModel = scaler.fit(input_df)
scaled_input_df = scalerModel.transform(input_df)

# Split the data into training and test sets (80 , 20 rule)
(training_df, test_df) = scaled_input_df.randomSplit([0.8, 0.2])

training_df.show()
test_df.show()

%pyspark
def Training(trainDF):
	print("Training began")
	logisticRegression = LogisticRegression(labelCol="popularity", featuresCol="scaledFeatures",elasticNetParam=0.8, family="multinomial",maxIter=100)
	model=logisticRegression.fit(trainDF)
	print("Training stoped")
	return model 
	
model = Training(training_df)

# prdict
predictions = model.transform(test_df)

# predicted data 
predictions.select("prediction", "popularity", "features").show(50)

%pyspark
#Q4.6
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

owners = spark.sql("select host_id, host_name, COUNT(*) as rentals from tempory_view group by host_id, host_name Order by rentals DESC")
total_owners=owners.count()


multiple_rental_owners = spark.sql("select host_id, host_name, COUNT(*) as rentals from tempory_view group by host_id, host_name HAVING rentals>1 Order by rentals DESC")
total_multiple_rental_owners=multiple_rental_owners.count()
multiple_owners_percentage = (float(total_multiple_rental_owners)/total_owners)*100.0
print("Percentage of owners own more than one propert: ")
print(multiple_owners_percentage)

labels = 'Multiple property owners', 'Single property owners'
sizes = [multiple_owners_percentage, 100 - multiple_owners_percentage]
explode = (0.1,0)
fig1, ax1 = plt.subplots()
ax1.pie(sizes, explode=explode, labels=labels, autopct='%1.1f%%',
        shadow=True, startangle=90)
ax1.axis('equal')
plt.show()
